  "details": "Bundler manages an application&apos;s dependencies through its entire life, across many machines, systematically and repeatably.\r\n\r\nSecurity Fix(es):\r\n\r\nBundler prior to 2.1.0 uses a predictable path in /tmp/, created with insecure permissions as a storage location for gems, if locations under the user&apos;s home directory are not available. If Bundler is used in a scenario where the user does not have a writable home directory, an attacker could place malicious code in this directory that would be later loaded and executed.(CVE-2019-3881)",
